Package stocker.controller.database

Class DatabaseController

  • java.lang.Object
    • stocker.controller.inputoutput.Serializer
      • stocker.controller.inputoutput.NetworkClient
        • stocker.controller.database.DatabaseController
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DatabaseActionListener, PropertiesListener
    public class DatabaseController
extends NetworkClient
implements DatabaseActionListener, PropertiesListener
    The database controller acts as an intermediary between the model of the data provider and the database model. By expanding the NetworkClient class, the database controller has the ability to import data via REST web services (PullClient) and communicate via web sockets (PushClient). The NetworkClient communicates directly with the provider and converts the raw JSON data into the corresponding classes specified by the provider. The methods retrieveSearchDataForGeneral(String, DisplayType) and retrieveSearchDataForSymbol(String, DisplayType) implement a search query for a general “search word” and for a special share via symbol. retrievePullQuoteDataForSymbol(String) sends a request for the “Quote” data of a stock and retrievePullDataForSymbol(String, TimeInterval) sends a request for stock data for a specific stock. These 4 called “retriever” methods use SwingWorker threading for their respective HTTP requests. If the data is received successfully, they transfer the data to the database model. If the data cannot be accessed, this is also noted in the database model. The method onPushDataMessage(PushData) receives the real-time data, checks its usability and transfers it to the data model. In addition to methods for starting / stopping, connect / disconnect, subscribe requests, there is a method, onDataProviderChange(DataProviderProfile), which initiates the server change. First, the new data provider is assigned, during “shutdown” (shutdownDatabase ()) the connection to the server is also disconnected and the existing data is set to the stock data state type unclear (resetStockDataState ()). When “booting” (bootDatabase ()), the database is first connected to the new server, then the new data provider is queried for the existing stock names and, if necessary, the data is loaded.
    Author:
    Christoph Kaplan
